				<td class="PanelBodyAlternate"><span class="SmallBoldText">Re: how can I get help for trak?<a name="70926"/></span><br><span class="SmallText"> Posted: </span><span class="SmallText">Dec 12 04 4:48 AM</span></td>
			</tr><tr>
				<td colspan="2"><span>Try finding another high level bard and befriend him without being too much of a pain.  All the better if the bard you befriend is in a large guild.  Right now is a good time with people exploring EQ2 and WoW once your new bard friend is comfortable with you.  Ask if he and some of his high level friends would be willing to do a UDB (undead bard) raid sometime and explain your plight.
<br />

<br />
It has worked on me before.  I have pulled together raids or gave the young bard someone who was able to assist them.
<br />

<br />
Don't over due it or the bard may become hostile.</span></td>
